subjective judgement to modify effectiveness parameters.
CONCLUSIONS: Frailty assessment may be good value for money. However, limited 
availability of geriatric consultation services, may hinder implementation. 
Thus, the estimated benefits of frailty screening may not be achievable in 
practice.

